Stormwind <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/01 3:30:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Twinks and Powerlevelers.... :-/</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry Kaz, I sympathize with your frustration, but can't support your arguments.<br>
<br>
You say it hurts everyone in the zone when two are killing the amount of wisps that five would kill. Wrong. It hurts you because you wanted to hunt wisps. You want the wisps (for the same reason they do, experience and loot) and can't have them, so you're mad.<br>
<br>
You imply that the two are being dishonest in their hunting tactics. This seems like a rationalization of your frustration to me. What is so morally reprehensible about a high level pulling monsters to a low level? You've already admitted you have no problem with it, if it's done somewhere where it doesn't interfere with your hunting.<br>
<br>
Your arguments and frustration all keep coming back to the simple fact that you wanted the choice monsters in the choice spot, and couldn't have them.<br>
<br>
I've wanted choice monsters in choice spots and not been able to have them too, that's one of the downsides of playing in a large multiplayer environment. One of the upsides, is that you can get help hunting from your friends/guildmates and get hand-me-downs from your friends/guildmates. You call it dishonest twinking and powerleveling. I call it being social and having fun with friends. Do I get frustrated when other people are in my way? Absolutely. But, I recognize that they have just as much right to enjoy themselves as I do, so I go do something else.<br>
<br>
Oh well, I have a feeling we'll never agree on this subject, since the debate has raged for years. I wish you the best Kaz, and the only reason I argue with you is that I feel if you could let go of your frustration with twinks/PLs it would let you relax and enjoy the game more.<br>
<br>
On the plus side, I often see many wisps in WC with no one hunting them on this server. So maybe the event that ticked you off will not happen very often to you here.<br>
<br>
Grimwyrd<br>
