<br>
But, getting bent out of shape cause someone is killing the wisps that YOU want to kill is also basically greedy. It comes back to YOU want the wisps, and you're mad cause someone else is getting them.<br>
<br>
It's real easy to point the finger and say someone else is being rude and greedy, but most people need to look in a mirror and realize that it's greed and envy that are driving their feelings too. People get mad cause they're not getting &quot;their fair share&quot; and pissed that the other person is getting &quot;more than their fair share&quot;. But the whole &quot;fair share&quot; concept is flawed.<br>
<br>
A 30th and 10th level team have just as much right to those wisps as anyone else, and it's greedy and rude to make them go to the ass-end of Kunark just so that they don't get in your way.<br>
<br>
That's the point I'm trying to make. This game is a lot more relaxing when you don't get caught up in what others are doing and just try to have fun. If you are in WC, see a wisp, want to kill a wisp...then, kill it. If there aren't wisps to kill, don't concern yourself with why.<br>
<br>
Maybe a 10th/30th team is hogging them, maybe there are five 12th levels soloing them...it doesn't matter. If there are not enough wisps to keep you happy, then do something else, don't get mad at the other people for ruining your gaming experience.<br>
<br>
The last time I tried to hunt wisps in WC, I wasn't finding very many. This shocked me, because there were only a couple people in the zone. It turned out that a ranger was tracking them down and taking them out. I didn't have tracking, so I couldn't compete with him. Did I get mad at the ranger for hogging the wisps? Did I get mad at him for getting about five kills to my one? No, of course not. I was a little frustrated that I was in the mood to hunt wisps and wasn't able to, but I found something else to do.<br>
<br>
Oh well, like I said. I'm just playing devil's advocate, because I think people let the actions of others bother them too much in this game.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
